Hello <@U01CD0VMBD3> ,
To overwrite your existing files ,you have to include overwrite flag in the end of above command.
hs fetch --account=<name> <src> [dest] --overwrite

For reference you can refer to this link and read about hs fetch command.
<https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/cms/developer-reference/local-development-cli>
The `<>` only denotes where your parameter is. You do not need to include that

Ideally workflow wise all developers on the project would be using your git project, and you would use that as the source of truth. Any time you make changes using the DM you would fetch them and commit them.

You should be committing changes as you make them vs doing large daily commits. That way when you read the commit message you know exactly what small detail was changed, and can use that to revert a commit later if something went wrong.
